	)
	(text "th = 0.693 x (R1 + R2) X C1\ntl = 0.693 X R2 X C1\n\nNeeded frequency = around 3-4Hz, 50% duty cycle\n\n3=Hz = 3 cycles per second = 1/6s on, 1/6 off, repeated 3 times\nin one second\n\n50% duty cycle means 50% of period high, 50% low, to achieve this, since tl is less time,\na diode is connected acrros R1 and C1 so when charging, it is only done through R1,\nand when discharging, it is only through R2. When R2 = R1, th = tl, using schottky diode\nand full GLV voltage makes duty cycle very close to 50%\n\nth = tl = 0.167, we can make C1 1.2uF and have R1 = R2 = 200k ohms = 0.16632s per tl and th"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 118.364 197.358 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "419854d0-95e2-4333-b68c-eef3af17ecea")
	)
